1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:01,810
(All characters, locations,
organizations, and incidents...)

2
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:03,580
(in this drama are fictional.)

3
00:00:03,580 --> 00:00:05,110
(This production followed
all guidelines for young actors.)

4
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:12,050
(Chief Kim Ji Hwan)

5
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:20,790
It's been a while, Chief Kim.

6
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:23,360
We've been a bit out of touch,
haven't we?

7
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:26,000
I'll be sending you
a little something soon...

8
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,200
to use generously
for the nation's sake.

9
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,570
Don't you worry about a thing.

10
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,910
The old man can't find out
that I've lost control...

11
00:00:37,910 --> 00:00:38,910
over the Swiss account.

12
00:00:40,180 --> 00:00:41,750
Otherwise, not only will
Kunhyang Group crumble,

13
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:45,080
but so will I, Jin Tae Seok.

14
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:48,120
I have to get it back,
no matter what.

15
00:00:48,990 --> 00:00:50,050
I absolutely must.

16
00:00:51,790 --> 00:00:53,020
(Episode 96)

17
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:05,270
From now on, you're Jin Jung won.

18
00:01:06,370 --> 00:01:08,510
My one and only successor.

19
00:01:11,910 --> 00:01:14,050
But does that mean
I trust you completely?

20
00:01:14,810 --> 00:01:15,880
Of course not.

21
00:01:18,150 --> 00:01:19,280
King Yeongjo...

22
00:01:20,650 --> 00:01:23,250
killed his own son
by locking him in a rice chest.

23
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:25,160
All for the sake of power.

24
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:28,390
I could do the same at any moment,

25
00:01:30,260 --> 00:01:32,200
but right now,
I have no other cards to play.

26
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:33,930
More importantly,

27
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:36,430
whether it was an act or not,

28
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,840
I need my own flesh and blood...

29
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:41,170
who'd at least pretend to die
for me.

30
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,080
Are you okay?

31
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:53,120
What about you, Father?

32
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:58,260
I'm just relieved you're okay.

33
00:01:59,090 --> 00:02:00,230
Jung Won,

34
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:03,700
did you know
the bottle was poisoned?

35
00:02:04,830 --> 00:02:06,660
I wasn't sure myself.

36
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,000
Se Mi told me.

37
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:12,440
She said Se Hoon
might have been the one.

38
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,810
You could have died.

39
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:16,710
Then why did you do it?

40
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:18,940
That's a good question.

41
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:22,550
I don't completely understand
myself either.

42
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:26,580
It's just that before I could
think it through,

43
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,190
my body moved first...

44
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:30,660
No,

45
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:35,290
my heart acted first.

46
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:40,160
Isn't that ridiculous?

47
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:44,170
It's still so awkward
calling you Father,

48
00:02:45,570 --> 00:02:48,410
and I can't stop thinking about
how you pushed me off that rooftop,

49
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:50,680
which makes my whole body tremble.

50
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:54,580
And yet, my heart...

51
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:58,020
is telling me I'd rather die
than watch you...

52
00:02:58,020 --> 00:03:00,290
Enough. That's all I need to hear.

53
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:06,090
You are the only successor
I will ever acknowledge.

54
00:03:06,790 --> 00:03:07,990
You've earned it.

55
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:12,500
Get some good rest for a few days.

56
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,100
Try not to think about anything.

57
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:16,630
My dear daughter, Jung Won.

58
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:30,780
A life-or-death lie?
I can do that all day long.

59
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:35,920
Because I am Jin Jung Won,
your one and only successor.

60
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:39,790
What? Cha Jung Won...

61
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:42,630
drank the poisoned liquor
instead of Jin Tae Seok?

62
00:03:43,430 --> 00:03:45,930
So, is she dead or alive?

63
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:50,440
Okay. Got it. Keep me posted.

64
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:56,110
Cha Jung Won has more lives
than a cat.

65
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,910
Isn't it just so touching?

66
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,650
What a devoted daughter,

67
00:04:01,650 --> 00:04:03,980
ready to die for her father
who tried to kill her.

68
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:06,080
Are you bringing up the folktale
about the devoted daughter?

69
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,320
How'd you know?

70
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:11,320
I know you like the back of my hand.

71
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:16,930
But my gut tells me
she's not playing that devoted role.

72
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:19,000
So it was all staged?

73
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:20,330
Exactly.

74
00:04:20,330 --> 00:04:23,330
I'm a master at that game.
I'm Crown Capital's top card sharp.

75
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:24,670
It's all a show.

76
00:04:24,670 --> 00:04:27,340
A show? Gosh, how touching.

77
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,510
Revenge she's willing to die for.

78
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:34,210
That reminds me, Yeong Soo.
I need you to do something for me.

79
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:40,120
We need a Plan B if it goes south,
don't we?

80
00:04:40,590 --> 00:04:43,020
The slush fund that Han Hye Ra stole
from Jin Tae Seok.

81
00:04:43,290 --> 00:04:44,920
I'm going to take it all for myself.

82
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:46,760
How?

83
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:49,260
What do you mean, "how?"
You're going to get me the password.

84
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:51,700
Me?

85
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:04,510
Let's see.

86
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:09,510
What is this?
I bet Ha Neul knows it.

87
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,880
Darn it. What should I do?

88
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,990
Five, eight, six...

89
00:05:14,290 --> 00:05:15,950
- What are you doing?
- Gosh, you scared me.

90
00:05:16,590 --> 00:05:17,960
I'm not even in my room.

91
00:05:19,090 --> 00:05:20,120
I'm just...

92
00:05:20,490 --> 00:05:22,130
What are you trying to dig up now?

93
00:05:22,590 --> 00:05:24,960
What am I, a miner?
What would I be digging for?

94
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:28,800
Next time, just ask me.

95
00:05:28,970 --> 00:05:32,100
Really? Fine,
then I'll just ask you now.

96
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:35,540
According to Han Hye Ra,

97
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:37,740
she said you guys stole
the slush fund...

98
00:05:37,740 --> 00:05:39,340
Jin Tae Seok had hidden away.

99
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:41,710
How did you do it?

100
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:45,350
You're not involved with a syndicate
or something, are you? Right?

101
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:46,850
It's better if you don't know.

102
00:05:48,290 --> 00:05:49,290
I need to rest.

103
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:53,560
What?

104
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:57,500
You want me to leave?
Okay, fine. I'm going.

105
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,800
- I'm going.
- Go on. Get out.

106
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,800
Goodness, all right.

107
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:11,340
What are you doing in my study?

108
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:14,780
Did you see Jung Won?

109
00:06:15,710 --> 00:06:16,780
Just now.

110
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,780
It feels so strange.

111
00:06:20,490 --> 00:06:21,520
What does?

112
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:24,860
Jung Won did something I couldn't.

113
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:29,490
To think she'd drink poison for you,

114
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:31,760
the very person
who tried to hurt her.

115
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,660
She's my daughter.

116
00:06:34,530 --> 00:06:35,770
A child...

117
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:39,170
must protect their parents,
even at the cost of their own life.

118
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:40,810
What about the parents?

119
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:44,240
- What?
- Shouldn't the parents...

120
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,510
also risk their lives
for their children?

121
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:52,250
There are children worth dying for.
Take Se Mi, for example.

122
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:53,680
Unlike you,

123
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:56,820
I wouldn't risk my life
for the black sheep of the family.

124
00:06:57,420 --> 00:07:00,190
How could you drink poison
for a child like that?

125
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:02,330
I know.

126
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:04,500
Especially these days.

127
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:05,960
Why?

128
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,430
Do you find her touching now...

129
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:11,570
because she took poison
for her father,

130
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:13,540
who tried to get rid of her?

131
00:07:13,910 --> 00:07:15,670
A part of me is relieved...

132
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:19,540
that you seem to see that girl
in a different light now.

133
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,680
- And another part of me...
- Is jealous?

134
00:07:22,810 --> 00:07:23,880
Jealous?

135
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:26,350
Between a mother and daughter?
That's ridiculous.

136
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:30,560
Are you really going to let...

137
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,460
Jung Won inherit Kunhyang Group?

138
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:37,030
Seeing you get jealous...

139
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,300
actually makes me feel a lot better.

140
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:49,470
(Kunhyang Group)

141
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:25,640
What do you think you're doing?

142
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:31,880
Vice Chairman Jin Se Hoon,
you are dismissed, effective today.

143
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,320
What?

144
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:38,360
The Honorary Chairman also ordered
that you be removed from succession.

145
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:42,230
(Vice Chairman Jin Se Hoon
Dismissed)

146
00:08:42,290 --> 00:08:43,730
(Dismissal Confirmed
by the Board of Directors)

147
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:48,170
It appears the decision was made
during an emergency board meeting.

148
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:51,870
Now they're even kicking me out
of the company?

149
00:08:52,970 --> 00:08:54,670
Says who?

150
00:08:56,970 --> 00:08:58,480
(Chairman Gong Nan Sook)

151
00:08:59,310 --> 00:09:02,210
Ma'am, I've landed a big one!

152
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,680
- Did you really find it?
- Yes.

153
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,720
My goodness.

154
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:11,290
For such a clever boy,
you're so old-school.

155
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:15,290
Old school is the safest.
Make sure you don't lose it.

156
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:18,360
But how did you find out?

157
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:20,800
While checking
Chairman Joo Ha Neul's laptop,

158
00:09:20,930 --> 00:09:23,270
I found evidence of a spy app...

159
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:25,970
he installed on Honorary Chairman
Jin Tae Seok's computer.

160
00:09:25,970 --> 00:09:27,000
A spy app?

161
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,040
It's a type of hacking app.

162
00:09:29,910 --> 00:09:32,380
Ha Neul knows how to hack?

163
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:35,110
Is there anything he can't do?

164
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:38,780
It's pretty basic for people
who are good with computers.

165
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:42,420
Listen to you showing off.
And then what?

166
00:09:42,420 --> 00:09:44,620
I used a similar method myself.

167
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:19,520
My goodness. That's amazing.
You're really something else.

168
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:22,960
I accessed the logs
from when Chairman Joo ran the spy app...

169
00:10:23,030 --> 00:10:25,730
and pulled every single keystroke
he made.

170
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:29,030
I pulled an all-nighter to get it.

171
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:34,270
Great job. This is the biggest thing
you've pulled off in a long time.

172
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,340
Good work.

173
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:39,740
All right, then,
let's make the transfer, shall we?

174
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:43,850
If we move over ten million dollars
at once, it'll trigger an alert.

175
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:46,380
- What should we do?
- How else?

176
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:47,990
We'll do it little by little.

177
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:50,120
We'll just siphon it off
in smaller chunks.

178
00:10:52,490 --> 00:10:53,620
Mom.

179
00:10:54,430 --> 00:10:56,130
Do you know that Cha Jung Won
is the Kunhyang successor?

180
00:10:56,190 --> 00:10:58,460
That came out of left field.

181
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:01,130
What? Ha Neul is doing great
as the chairman.

182
00:11:01,130 --> 00:11:02,270
What are you talking about?

183
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:05,070
The family kicked Se Hoon out.
It's a total mess over there!

184
00:11:09,410 --> 00:11:13,110
It's a darn good thing
I swiped that password when I did.

185
00:11:13,210 --> 00:11:14,450
What's my next move?

186
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:21,420
While my daughter, Jung Won,
trains as my successor,

187
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:24,420
don't you think she deserve a title
befitting her status?

188
00:11:24,590 --> 00:11:28,030
My position as a designer is enough,
Honorary Chairman.

189
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:30,430
What about
the vacant Vice Chairman post?

190
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:31,960
That's too much.

191
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:34,670
Jung Won is
a highly qualified designer.

192
00:11:34,870 --> 00:11:37,740
And she wants to further her success
in that field.

193
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,340
I think Chief Director
of the Design Team...

194
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:41,610
would be a fitting role.

195
00:11:41,970 --> 00:11:43,370
That's a good idea.

196
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:47,280
And Chairman Han can't be sidelined,
can she?

197
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:51,980
Exactly. I'd like to recommend her
for the position of group advisor.

198
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,190
I agree.

199
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,620
I do as well.

200
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:01,060
Let's put it on the board's agenda
and get it approved.

201
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,240
You're telling me to get a divorce?

202
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:14,910
No wonder
she was acting so strangely.

203
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:16,770
Turns out she's pregnant.

204
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:18,810
Young Chae is pregnant?

205
00:12:19,510 --> 00:12:23,110
- Is that true?
- Yes. And it's for real this time.

206
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:25,620
But Young Chae...

207
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:29,390
is not one to ruin her life
on some broke guy with no future.

208
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:30,990
Are you going to treat me...

209
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:33,290
like scum too,
like everyone else is now?

210
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:37,630
Goodness, must you be so crude?

211
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:40,870
No matter how I look at it,

212
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,730
you and Young Chae...

213
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:45,200
- will never work. It's over.
- I won't do it.

214
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:48,840
You're the one who threw a fit,
screaming you didn't want her.

215
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,040
Young Chae is the only one...

216
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:55,180
- who understands me.
- That "understanding you" thing...

217
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:58,580
means absolutely nothing.

218
00:12:58,950 --> 00:13:00,050
What about the baby?

219
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:06,520
I'll register the baby under my name
and raise it as my own.

220
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,700
I will never forget...

221
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:15,570
this humiliation.

222
00:13:16,570 --> 00:13:18,400
As for Young Chae
and our unborn child,

223
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:22,410
I'll entrust them to your care
for now.

224
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:30,380
We've mostly finished
with the urgent restructuring.

225
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:32,120
Now, it's Joo Ha Neul's turn.

226
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:36,050
Joo Ha Neul.

227
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,220
Can you take him down yourself?

228
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:42,690
My place is wherever you point me,
Father.

229
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,860
It won't matter who's there.
They'll be invisible to me.

230
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:48,900
You really are ruthless.

231
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:55,170
But the old geezers on the board
have already turned on me.

232
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:57,440
I don't know about the rest,
but the chairmanship is a tough fight.

233
00:13:57,510 --> 00:13:59,210
Don't try to win their trust.

234
00:13:59,610 --> 00:14:00,680
Instead,

235
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:03,550
give them a reason
they can't refuse.

236
00:14:03,810 --> 00:14:05,020
A reason?

237
00:14:05,950 --> 00:14:07,080
Fear.

238
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:08,690
Fear...

239
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:10,450
Specifically?

240
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:14,120
If the board won't listen,
we can bring in outside forces.

241
00:14:14,990 --> 00:14:19,030
Forces that threaten their positions
and their very livelihoods.

242
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:22,970
Fight fire with fire, you mean?

243
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:26,670
Many people in politics
and business owe you.

244
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:30,070
You know exactly whose pockets
that money lined,

245
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:32,040
and I'm certain...

246
00:14:32,340 --> 00:14:35,010
that you have the records
to prove it.

247
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:38,620
The money may disappear,

248
00:14:38,620 --> 00:14:40,250
but even a king
can't erase the trail.

249
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:44,920
I could bring this whole country
to its knees with a single word.

250
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,090
It's time to reap what I've sown.

251
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:52,530
I'll give you some names on my list.
You're going to deliver my message.

252
00:14:52,830 --> 00:14:54,770
Teach those old geezers
on the board...

253
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:56,300
who are defying me a lesson.

254
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:05,280
Jin Tae Seok definitely has a list
of his slush fund transactions.

255
00:15:05,540 --> 00:15:07,280
I've already confirmed
a few names on it.

256
00:15:08,650 --> 00:15:11,650
Jung Won, he must be dead set
on making you his successor.

257
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:13,620
Considering he's willing to show you
his darkest secrets.

258
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:16,190
He asked me...

259
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:19,460
if I could take down
Chairman Joo Ha Neul.

260
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:22,360
I knew it. What did you say?

261
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,400
I told him I could.

262
00:15:25,530 --> 00:15:26,760
Good.

263
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,300
Don't hesitate.

264
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,800
My head knows that,

265
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:32,240
but the moment the words
left my mouth,

266
00:15:32,540 --> 00:15:34,200
I hated myself.

267
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,810
It's all an act.

268
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:43,080
I'll let myself fall
all the way to the bottom...

269
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:45,580
so you can secure a perfect victory.

270
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:50,990
I'll see this through to the end.

271
00:15:51,690 --> 00:15:52,860
And I won't lose you either.

272
00:15:56,230 --> 00:15:58,030
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

273
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:02,930
Hey, what about Jung Won?
Why haven't I seen her around here?

274
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,230
She's been busy.

275
00:16:04,940 --> 00:16:05,940
Why is that?

276
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:11,880
She is now the successor...

277
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,780
to Honorary Chairman Jin Tae Seok.

278
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:14,950
What are you talking about?

279
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:17,650
- Whose successor?
- You know who I'm talking about.

280
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:19,650
Things will be back to normal soon.

281
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:21,690
Everything will be back
where it belongs.

282
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:24,520
Still, there's a line
you just don't cross.

283
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:26,490
Jin Tae Seok's successor?

284
00:16:27,290 --> 00:16:28,430
That girl, Jung Won...

285
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:30,660
Why does she
have to drive me crazy again?

286
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:46,040
(Chief Kim)

287
00:16:49,950 --> 00:16:51,010
This is Han Hye Ra.

288
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:54,790
What a surprise to hear from you.

289
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:59,460
Yes. By "the list," you mean...

290
00:17:01,190 --> 00:17:03,290
Yes. I suspected as much,

291
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:06,100
but I don't think we should
discuss it over the phone.

292
00:17:08,530 --> 00:17:10,830
Yes, I'll see you tomorrow.

293
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:16,510
The old man...

294
00:17:18,010 --> 00:17:20,280
is starting to distrust
Jin Tae Seok.

295
00:17:29,450 --> 00:17:31,460
(Kunhyang Group)

296
00:17:31,820 --> 00:17:34,390
Have the boycotts from civic groups
died down?

297
00:17:34,530 --> 00:17:38,130
We sent statements on our position
to each group and began a dialogue.

298
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:41,800
Most have agreed to suspend
their boycotts.

299
00:17:41,870 --> 00:17:44,030
Thanks to Chief Director Cha
working behind the scenes,

300
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,200
everything is going off
without a hitch.

301
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,340
I think we can all breathe
a sigh of relief.

302
00:17:48,540 --> 00:17:53,280
That's the owner's family for you.
A great sense of responsibility!

303
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,450
What do you mean,
"behind the scenes?"

304
00:17:56,110 --> 00:17:58,880
The most important thing right now
is to regain the public's trust.

305
00:17:59,020 --> 00:18:01,320
And to do that,
we must ensure objectivity.

306
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:05,490
Public perception is unforgiving.

307
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,360
Things may calm down for now,

308
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:09,290
but public outrage could flare up
again at any moment.

309
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:12,460
Isn't that exactly what you wanted,
Chairman Joo?

310
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:16,900
- What are you implying?
- The one who gains the most...

311
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:18,800
is you, isn't it,
Chairman Joo Ha Neul?

312
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:21,270
(Kunhyang Group)

313
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:22,940
I was told that
when the stock price fell,

314
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:25,740
you acquired
a substantial amount of shares.

315
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:27,340
Using borrowed names, no less.

316
00:18:28,180 --> 00:18:29,510
Is that true?

317
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:32,850
That's a misunderstanding.
Borrowed names? Of course not.

318
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,180
But what if it is true?

319
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:37,720
What's to stop you from
completely dismantling Kunhyang...

320
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,390
after you buy it out for
a rock-bottom price, Chairman Joo?

321
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:40,460
Chief Director Cha!

322
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:42,590
This means you hid your identity
all this time,

323
00:18:42,590 --> 00:18:44,330
slowly plotting
to take the empire...

324
00:18:44,330 --> 00:18:46,730
the Kunhyang Family built
for yourself.

325
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,930
It's a chilling thought, isn't it?

326
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,870
You're awfully cocky,

327
00:18:51,870 --> 00:18:53,140
relying on
the Honorary Chairman Jin Tae Seok.

328
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:54,610
Excuse me?

329
00:18:54,610 --> 00:18:56,640
There are all these rumors
about you being the successor,

330
00:18:57,270 --> 00:18:58,380
but aren't you just his pawn?

331
00:18:58,380 --> 00:18:59,640
A pawn?

332
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:02,250
It's you who should be careful
with your words, Chairman Joo.

333
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:05,080
(Kunhyang Group)

334
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:09,550
I've realized I'm not Cha Jung Won,
but Jin Jung Won.

335
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:13,090
Kunhyang is my home and my family,
so of course I must protect it...

336
00:19:15,090 --> 00:19:16,330
from its enemies.

337
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,660
You're doing great.

338
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:22,370
Keep tearing me down, Jung Won.

339
00:19:24,370 --> 00:19:26,840
Ha Neul, I'm sorry.

340
00:19:47,420 --> 00:19:49,960
Chairman Joo,
keep an eye on the Swiss account.

341
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:52,060
Jin Tae Seok will catch on quickly,

342
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,200
and there's no telling what he'll do
to get it back.

343
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:15,950
The balance is different.

344
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:19,820
Someone has withdrawn
some of the money.

345
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:25,660
(Kunhyang Group)

346
00:20:25,730 --> 00:20:27,660
(Advisor Han Hye Ra)

347
00:20:31,670 --> 00:20:33,340
Who could have gotten to it already?

348
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,070
Jin Tae Seok,

349
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,310
or maybe Jin Se Hoon?

350
00:20:37,370 --> 00:20:40,240
They're both possibilities,
but we must investigate to confirm.

351
00:20:40,310 --> 00:20:42,610
Did word leak
from the Kunhyang Association?

352
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:45,080
What about the password?
Did you change it again?

353
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:46,820
Of course I did.

354
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:51,590
It looks like they took half
so it would be less noticeable.

355
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:54,420
Gong Nan Sook could be behind this.

356
00:20:55,530 --> 00:20:57,260
Let's deal with that later.

357
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:59,330
For now, this is top secret.

358
00:20:59,930 --> 00:21:02,400
I'm thinking of meeting someone
who can be a great asset to us.

359
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:09,970
He's the person behind the scenes
keeping Jin Tae Seok's power alive,

360
00:21:11,510 --> 00:21:14,080
and the one person who can also
take him down in one fell swoop.

361
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:16,110
He must be the biggest client...

362
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,680
of Jin Tae Seok’s slush fund.

363
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:20,950
Exactly.

364
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:23,950
As for me, I have to follow
Jin Tae Seok's orders...

365
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:26,420
and perfectly play the part
of the successor.

366
00:21:26,490 --> 00:21:29,790
Then, I'll figure out
who stole from the slush fund.

367
00:21:40,940 --> 00:21:43,210
I've booked the Moran Room,
Vice Chairman Jin.

368
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:51,980
Did you enjoy the meal?

369
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:53,980
Yes, it was delicious.

370
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:56,520
Chief Director Cha,
you must be very busy these days.

371
00:21:56,920 --> 00:22:01,390
Word is that Chairman Jin gave
his new successor full authority.

372
00:22:01,790 --> 00:22:05,030
That's an exaggeration.
The Chairman's still in charge.

373
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:07,760
Come on. He's an outsider
with no blood ties.

374
00:22:08,230 --> 00:22:09,930
He's nothing but a figurehead.

375
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:11,800
Wouldn't you agree, ma'am?

376
00:22:12,270 --> 00:22:14,570
There's nothing more powerful
than blood ties.

377
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:16,740
You really do resemble him.

378
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:18,910
You're the spitting image
of Chairman Jin.

379
00:22:25,780 --> 00:22:29,620
I heard Assemblyman Kang has been
under the weather a lot lately.

380
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:31,760
I'm told this works wonders
for colds.

381
00:22:46,770 --> 00:22:49,340
Chief Director Cha,
how very thoughtful of you.

382
00:22:49,570 --> 00:22:51,940
I'll be sure to give this
to the Assemblyman.

383
00:22:52,180 --> 00:22:56,280
From now on,
I will handle all Kunhyang matters.

384
00:23:18,270 --> 00:23:20,070
Managing Director Jung,
Director Park.

385
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,540
How dare they stand me up?

386
00:23:23,610 --> 00:23:25,340
So they'll only deal with
the successor now?

387
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:33,580
Not a single one of them
ever says no.

388
00:23:34,250 --> 00:23:35,590
That's how it always is.

389
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:38,190
They'd even risk their lives
for that parliamentary badge.

390
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:41,420
Isn't your family no different?

391
00:23:42,990 --> 00:23:44,960
I'm not denying it.

392
00:23:45,130 --> 00:23:47,460
Does it not occur to you
that you're all putting...

393
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:48,830
nooses around your own necks?

394
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:52,940
Even if the danger is obvious,
we'll still snatch the bait.

395
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:54,810
We gobble it up
and worry about it later.

396
00:23:56,340 --> 00:23:57,940
As for the list I gave you,

397
00:23:58,210 --> 00:23:59,880
please continue
to arrange the meetings.

398
00:24:02,850 --> 00:24:05,820
Chief Director Cha.
You've really changed.

399
00:24:06,420 --> 00:24:08,790
- I have?
- The look in your eyes,

400
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:10,750
the way you talk...

401
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,090
You're a completely different person
from before.

402
00:24:13,590 --> 00:24:14,690
I'm glad to hear that.

403
00:24:15,130 --> 00:24:17,360
I never want to go back
to who I was before.

404
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:20,960
The old me
didn't belong at Kunhyang Group.

405
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:23,570
After all,
I'm the heir to Kunhyang now.

406
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:57,000
I wasn't expecting you
to ask for a meeting.

407
00:24:57,070 --> 00:24:59,700
It's been a while,
Chairman Han Hye Ra.

408
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:01,610
I'm just an advisor now.

409
00:25:01,740 --> 00:25:04,070
And how is Honorary Chairman Jin?

410
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:06,840
What is it you want to know?

411
00:25:06,910 --> 00:25:09,410
He's not one to break a promise.

412
00:25:10,150 --> 00:25:13,550
- Maybe he likes making us squirm.
- What if he's not unwilling,

413
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:16,690
but because he can't?

414
00:25:30,970 --> 00:25:33,900
Sounds to me like the Swiss account
has been compromised.

415
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:36,310
That's not it, is it?

416
00:25:37,270 --> 00:25:39,440
It certainly has been a long time.

417
00:25:40,780 --> 00:25:43,680
You and my husband go way back.

418
00:25:44,250 --> 00:25:47,220
- Why bring up the past so suddenly?
- And with time,

419
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:51,390
wouldn't it be nice
if our trust deepened as well?

420
00:25:51,450 --> 00:25:54,320
Even those who are close
should be more courteous.

421
00:25:54,990 --> 00:25:57,630
My boss is an impatient man.

422
00:25:57,690 --> 00:26:00,960
Please give us another week.

423
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,170
A whole week?

424
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:07,540
Does Honorary Chairman
Jin Tae seok think of me,

425
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:10,270
or my boss,
as someone he can take for granted?

426
00:26:19,150 --> 00:26:21,050
That should be enough time
to think it over.

427
00:26:24,220 --> 00:26:25,920
We have to be the ones to find...

428
00:26:26,990 --> 00:26:28,220
the rest of the missing slush fund.

429
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:35,470
Spending money is so exhausting,
I can't even.

430
00:26:35,830 --> 00:26:37,170
I'm exhausted.

431
00:26:37,970 --> 00:26:41,870
But really, shopping is the best.
I absolutely love this.

432
00:26:41,940 --> 00:26:43,610
I give models a run for their money,
right?

433
00:26:43,610 --> 00:26:44,670
(Chairman Gong Nan Sook)

434
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:48,040
I didn't risk my life so you could
clean out that Swiss account...

435
00:26:48,110 --> 00:26:50,350
just so you could "flex"
while you shop.

436
00:26:50,510 --> 00:26:54,150
What? I barely spent a dime.
It was a drop in the bucket.

437
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:58,520
Are you pouting just because
I only bought you one outfit?

438
00:27:00,360 --> 00:27:03,060
Money is meant to be spent.
That makes the world go round.

439
00:27:03,660 --> 00:27:06,830
And for a woman, fashion is life.

440
00:27:06,930 --> 00:27:08,730
It's all about the flex, you know?

441
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:12,100
That's not my point.
Honestly, the money Jin Tae Seok...

442
00:27:12,170 --> 00:27:14,300
stashed away was from all sorts of
shady deals, wasn't it?

443
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:15,970
So? What's your point?

444
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:19,840
Even if you can't give it back
to the community or something,

445
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:24,850
- we could donate it to the needy.
- A donation?

446
00:27:25,250 --> 00:27:28,450
Sure. You can donate
your money when you make it big.

447
00:27:28,650 --> 00:27:32,190
Who are you to tell me what to do?
This is my money now.

448
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:33,690
And I'll do whatever I want with it.

449
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:36,330
You've got to be kidding me.

450
00:27:37,290 --> 00:27:38,930
So it was you, Gong Nan Sook.
I knew it.

451
00:27:39,330 --> 00:27:42,770
When did you sneak in here again
so quietly?

452
00:27:43,330 --> 00:27:45,700
Did word get out that I bought out
a whole floor...

453
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:46,840
of the Kunhyang Department store?

454
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:48,370
Who called and tattled on me?

455
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:50,410
Having fun shopping
with stolen money?

456
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:51,740
Having a good time?

457
00:27:52,410 --> 00:27:53,440
Stolen?

458
00:27:53,740 --> 00:27:55,250
You can't just say
whatever you want.

459
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:56,810
You stole half...

460
00:27:56,810 --> 00:27:59,220
from Jin Tae Seok's Swiss account,
didn't you?

461
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:01,480
- I told you, I didn't.
- Just tell me the truth.

462
00:28:02,190 --> 00:28:03,290
You know you stole it.

463
00:28:03,350 --> 00:28:07,460
I didn't steal it.
I just took half off the top.

464
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:10,490
- Wasn't it the obvious move?
- What?

465
00:28:11,690 --> 00:28:14,700
We didn't take that money
from Jin Tae Seok for you to spend.

466
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:18,940
It was to expose the ugly truth
behind Jin Tae Seok's power.

467
00:28:19,570 --> 00:28:22,310
To expose his ugly truth,

468
00:28:22,810 --> 00:28:26,240
you don't need trillions of won.
The amount doesn't matter.

469
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:29,980
Besides, did you think that I,
Gong Nan Sook, obsessed with money,

470
00:28:30,380 --> 00:28:34,020
would just let three trillion won
sit there untouched?

471
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:38,390
So the temptation was too much
to resist?

472
00:28:38,590 --> 00:28:42,990
Yes! Do you have any idea
how hard I struggled to resist?

473
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:45,860
I was going to take it all,

474
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:49,400
but out of the goodness of my heart,
I only took half.

475
00:28:49,470 --> 00:28:52,800
Gong Nan Sook, that's illicit money.

476
00:28:53,170 --> 00:28:55,470
If this gets out,
you'll end up in handcuffs.

477
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:59,080
Handcuffs? You mean like bracelets?
The price of silver is sky-high.

478
00:28:59,140 --> 00:29:00,840
Think of it as a good investment.
What's the big deal?

479
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:03,910
Cut the crap and cough it up!

480
00:29:04,650 --> 00:29:05,650
Not a chance.

481
00:29:06,180 --> 00:29:08,950
I take money,
and I never pay it back.

482
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:12,020
That's the iron rule.

483
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:15,790
Is that money more important to you
than Joo Ha Neul? Is it?

484
00:29:16,830 --> 00:29:19,530
Ha Neul or the money?
That is the question.

485
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:25,600
Actually, Ha Neul needs the money.
I choose the money. The money.

486
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:29,310
Fine. Then I guess I'll just have to
go and tell Joo Ha Neul.

487
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:31,470
About what you've done.

488
00:29:31,740 --> 00:29:33,780
Hye Ra! Han Hye Ra!

489
00:29:35,150 --> 00:29:36,150
Darn it.

490
00:29:36,850 --> 00:29:40,720
If Ha Neul finds out, he'll flip.
What am I going to do?

491
00:29:41,220 --> 00:29:42,990
Whatever. Money comes first.

492
00:29:43,450 --> 00:29:46,920
I have a bad feeling about this.
It's killing me.

493
00:29:48,530 --> 00:29:49,530
What's this?

494
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:01,500
For crying out loud.

495
00:30:02,070 --> 00:30:03,610
You're all I have left.

496
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:05,480
Please, you have to help me.

497
00:30:07,710 --> 00:30:11,110
Mom, please help Se Hoon. Please?

498
00:30:11,510 --> 00:30:14,920
The rumors about you were so bad,
I was worried it'd make me look bad.

499
00:30:15,190 --> 00:30:18,250
So out of pity,
I helped you out, let you stay,

500
00:30:18,660 --> 00:30:20,720
and now you're demanding
everything I've got?

501
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:22,930
The whole world has turned
its back on me.

502
00:30:24,630 --> 00:30:27,300
If you don't help me,
no one else will...

503
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:36,140
- For Young Chae's sake, please...
- I'm already in hot water myself.

